fix(i18n): hide Google banner + instant in-place language switch

- MutationObserver removes iframe.goog-te-banner-frame on sight
  (CSS alone wasn't fast enough; iframe is injected after init).
- gfApplyLanguage now triggers the hidden widget select change event
  for instant in-place translation when switching te/hi/ta/kn — no
  location.reload on the current page.
- Reload still used when switching back to English (only way to
  restore the source DOM in-place).
- Stronger CSS forces body top to 0 and position static to prevent
  the layout shift Google adds.

MPA page-to-page navigation still triggers a fresh page load (browser
behaviour) but each new page reads the googtrans cookie and translates
automatically. The brief visible flash before translation completes is
unavoidable without a full SPA refactor.

Cache-bust v=20260519k.
